262
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:08,920
 Everything's been burnt down.

263
00:10:08,920 --> 00:10:10,840
 There's just rubble and ashes

264
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:12,480
 and there's nothing beautiful.

265
00:10:12,480 --> 00:10:18,000
 And it's in this space that God commissions Zerubbabel.

266
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:18,920
 I'm gonna read it to you.

267
00:10:18,920 --> 00:10:21,400
 He says this, "So the Lord stirred up

268
00:10:21,400 --> 00:10:24,200
 "in the spirit of Zerubbabel, governor of Judah,

269
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:28,280
 "and the spirit of Joshua, son of Josedach, the high priest,

270
00:10:28,280 --> 00:10:30,500
 "and the spirit of the whole remnant of the people.

271
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:32,680
 "They came and they began to work

272
00:10:32,680 --> 00:10:35,440
 "on the house of the Lord Almighty their God."

273
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:37,360
 It's found in Haggai.

274
00:10:37,360 --> 00:10:39,680
 So they get back and everything is a mess.

275
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:40,760
 There's nothing beautiful.

276
00:10:40,760 --> 00:10:43,760
 It's just rubble and it's terrible and there's nothing here.

277
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:46,840
 And God stirs in their spirit.

278
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:50,840
 He initiates it for them.

279
00:10:50,840 --> 00:10:51,840
 Think about this.

280
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:56,520
 God disrupts them and says, "I want you to do this thing.

281
00:10:56,520 --> 00:11:00,240
 "I want you guys to start building my temple again."

282
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:01,720
 God interrupts their plan.

283
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:02,880
 God intervenes into them.

284
00:11:02,880 --> 00:11:04,880
 He stirs their spirit.

285
00:11:04,880 --> 00:11:06,000
 This is good to remember.

286
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:09,260
 This whole temple thing is God's idea.

287
00:11:09,260 --> 00:11:11,880
 Like, it wasn't like they're like,

288
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:14,080
 "Oh, let's just be really good and let's build this."

289
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:17,800
 It's like God creates that desire in them

290
00:11:17,800 --> 00:11:19,280
 and commissions them.

291
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:22,600
 So God's idea given to them, go and do this.

292
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:24,760
 And I think for lots of us, when we have like the idea

293
00:11:24,760 --> 00:11:27,440
 of God's idea sending us to do something

294
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:29,540
 or God has led us into this thing,

295
00:11:29,540 --> 00:11:32,300
 we carry these preconceived ideas

296
00:11:32,300 --> 00:11:36,080
 that because it's God's idea, it's meant to be easy.

297
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:38,640
 I mean, I carry that a lot of times.

298
00:11:38,640 --> 00:11:40,600
 I have to regularly, I don't have to do anything.

299
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:42,760
 Actually, just living shows me clearly

300
00:11:42,760 --> 00:11:44,940
 that just because I'm following God's plan

301
00:11:44,940 --> 00:11:47,360
 does not mean it's gonna be easy.

302
00:11:47,360 --> 00:11:49,320
 Sometimes I'm like, it becomes harder, right?

303
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:51,880
 Like sometimes not following God's plan is the easy way

304
00:11:51,880 --> 00:11:53,000
 and everything is going well,

305
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:54,880
 but then I follow God's plan, it's like difficulty,

306
00:11:54,880 --> 00:11:55,720
 difficulty, difficulty.

307
00:11:55,720 --> 00:11:57,640
 I'm like, what am I doing?

308
00:11:57,640 --> 00:11:58,920
 But that's how these people feel.

309
00:11:58,920 --> 00:12:01,280
 The spirit of God stirs in their heart

310
00:12:01,280 --> 00:12:04,320
 this desire to build, rebuild the temple.

311
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:09,980
 He interrupts their life and sets them on this course.

312
00:12:09,980 --> 00:12:13,280
 And I think their expectation is that,

313
00:12:13,280 --> 00:12:15,400
 okay, if God has commissioned us to do this,

314
00:12:15,400 --> 00:12:18,400
 if he stood it in our hearts, then let's do it.

315
00:12:18,400 --> 00:12:19,240
 It's gonna be great.

316
00:12:19,240 --> 00:12:20,860
 And they start to do it.

317
00:12:20,860 --> 00:12:22,200
 They expect for it to be easy.

318
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:24,040
 But if you were here a few months back,

319
00:12:24,040 --> 00:12:26,040
 you would have known that we as a Vine community

320
00:12:26,040 --> 00:12:28,640
 went through this series on the book of Ezra,

321
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:31,440
 looking at this very aspect of the story

322
00:12:31,440 --> 00:12:33,520
 where they go to rebuild and they get there

323
00:12:33,520 --> 00:12:35,880
 and they're literally standing in the rubble

324
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:37,160
 of the old temple.

325
00:12:37,160 --> 00:12:38,960
 Like talk about sad.

326
00:12:38,960 --> 00:12:41,400
 Like you're literally standing in the ruins of it.

327
00:12:41,400 --> 00:12:44,000
 And I'm sure there's disappointment and emotions

328
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:47,800
 and frustrations and hurt and anger and sadness.

329
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:50,800
 And it's from that space that they're supposed to build.

330
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:52,360
 And as they start building,

331
00:12:52,360 --> 00:12:55,600
 there's those who are remembering how beautiful

332
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:57,720
 and how great and how much splendor

333
00:12:57,720 --> 00:12:59,400
 the old temple used to have.

334
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:00,800
 The presence of God used to be here.

335
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:03,340
 Solomon, who was the richest king of his day,

336
00:13:03,340 --> 00:13:05,000
 built this magnificent temple.

337
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:07,720
 It was beautiful to look at.

338
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:08,960
 And here they are standing in rubble

339
00:13:08,960 --> 00:13:09,880
 trying to like rebuild it.

340
00:13:09,880 --> 00:13:13,220
 So you have those who were like literally weeping.

341
00:13:13,220 --> 00:13:16,040
 Then you have those who were like worshiping

342
00:13:16,040 --> 00:13:18,800
 because the idea of building God's temple

343
00:13:18,800 --> 00:13:20,600
 and the presence of God being back with his people,

344
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:21,720
 they could see this future hope.

345
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:23,300
 So you've got this weeping and wailing

346
00:13:23,300 --> 00:13:26,100
 and worshiping happening side by side

347
00:13:26,100 --> 00:13:27,200
 while standing in the rubble.

348
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:29,360
 And then people start coming against them.

349
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:31,640
 People start trying to prevent them

350
00:13:31,640 --> 00:13:33,920
 from building the temple.

351
00:13:33,920 --> 00:13:35,800
 So now they're getting more obstacles and more obstacles.

352
00:13:35,800 --> 00:13:37,680
 And Pastor Andrew took us through a four-week series

353
00:13:37,680 --> 00:13:38,500
 looking at this.

354
00:13:38,500 --> 00:13:41,640
 But I wanna take us through what happens after all of that.

355
00:13:41,640 --> 00:13:45,160
 So they go through these obstacles

356
00:13:45,160 --> 00:13:46,880
 and eventually they reach a point where they're like,

357
00:13:46,880 --> 00:13:48,000
 we just can't do it.

358
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:52,360
 This desire that God had stirred in their hearts

359
00:13:52,360 --> 00:13:53,860
 looks impossible.

360
00:13:53,860 --> 00:13:55,400
 There's nothing that's making it happen.

361
00:13:55,400 --> 00:13:58,320
 Every step there's difficulty and there's frustration

362
00:13:58,320 --> 00:14:00,840
 and there's people against us and situations against us.

363
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:01,840
 So they quit.

364
00:14:01,840 --> 00:14:02,660
 They let it go.

365
00:14:02,660 --> 00:14:03,500
 They just let it.

366
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:04,400
 They don't disobey God.

367
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:05,800
 They just stop obeying God.

368
00:14:05,800 --> 00:14:09,480
 They let the dream die.

369
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:13,300
 They let it lie dormant for about 20 years.

370
00:14:13,300 --> 00:14:16,480
 And actually this is a really fascinating story.

371
00:14:16,480 --> 00:14:17,720
 I can't go into it here.

372
00:14:17,720 --> 00:14:18,960
 But they end up start,

373
00:14:18,960 --> 00:14:20,680
 they start building their own lives.

374
00:14:20,680 --> 00:14:21,620
 They start rebuilding again.

375
00:14:21,620 --> 00:14:24,120
 They've come back to their exiled land

376
00:14:24,120 --> 00:14:25,000
 where they were exiled from

377
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:25,960
 and they're like building their lives

378
00:14:25,960 --> 00:14:28,280
 and God's like, you're building your own life

379
00:14:28,280 --> 00:14:29,120
 but what about the temple?

380
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:30,240
 But that was too big for them.

381
00:14:30,240 --> 00:14:31,080
 So they gave up on it.

382
00:14:31,080 --> 00:14:32,920
 They let it go for 20 years.

383
00:14:32,920 --> 00:14:33,840
 So they're living in the land,

384
00:14:33,840 --> 00:14:38,000
 building up their lives with no temple for 20 years.

385
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:40,580
 And it's in that space that God breaks in

386
00:14:40,580 --> 00:14:43,480
 through the prophet of Zachariah,

387
00:14:43,480 --> 00:14:44,720
 speaking to the people,

388
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:49,680
 giving them perhaps the most important thing

389
00:14:49,680 --> 00:14:50,840
 that they were missing

390
00:14:50,840 --> 00:14:54,620
 when it came to following God and building his temple,

391
00:14:54,620 --> 00:14:56,020
 whether it be building his temple

392
00:14:56,020 --> 00:14:58,700
 or just being a follower of Yahweh.

393
00:14:58,700 --> 00:15:00,000
 Some crucial information.

394
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:03,280
 So I'm gonna read for us here in Zachariah chapter four,

395
00:15:03,280 --> 00:15:04,600
 starting at verse one.

396
00:15:04,600 --> 00:15:06,400
 This is a vision.

397
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:08,240
 So it's not gonna be like really clear.

398
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:10,400
 There's gonna be symbols and lamps and trees

399
00:15:10,400 --> 00:15:11,240
 and things like that.

400
00:15:11,240 --> 00:15:13,000
 But eventually we'll get to verse six

401
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:14,240
 where it'll be super clear.

402
00:15:14,240 --> 00:15:16,680
 Says this, "An angel who talked with me

403
00:15:16,680 --> 00:15:18,500
 "returned and woke me up.

404
00:15:18,500 --> 00:15:20,540
 "Like someone awakened from sleep.

405
00:15:20,540 --> 00:15:21,840
 "He asked me, what do you see?

406
00:15:21,840 --> 00:15:22,680
 "And I answered,

407
00:15:22,680 --> 00:15:25,820
 "I see a solid gold lamp stand with a bowl at the top

408
00:15:25,820 --> 00:15:27,360
 "and seven lamps on it,

409
00:15:27,360 --> 00:15:29,760
 "with seven channels to the lamps.

410
00:15:29,760 --> 00:15:32,200
 "Also, there are two olive trees by it,

411
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:33,540
 "one on the right of the bowl

412
00:15:33,540 --> 00:15:35,180
 "and the other on its left.

413
00:15:35,180 --> 00:15:37,120
 "I asked the angel who talked to me,

414
00:15:37,120 --> 00:15:38,600
 "what are these my Lord?

415
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:41,920
 "He answered, do you not know what these are?

416
00:15:41,920 --> 00:15:43,480
 "No, my Lord, I replied.

417
00:15:43,480 --> 00:15:44,680
 "So he said to me,

418
00:15:44,680 --> 00:15:47,420
 "this is the word of the Lord to Zerubbabel.

419
00:15:47,420 --> 00:15:50,660
 "Not by might nor by power,

420
00:15:50,660 --> 00:15:53,240
 "but by my spirit, says the Lord Almighty."

421
00:15:53,240 --> 00:15:54,080
 Let me pray.

422
00:15:54,080 --> 00:15:57,120
 God, we open your word

423
00:15:57,120 --> 00:16:01,780
 and we ask Holy Spirit that you would speak to our hearts.

424
00:16:01,780 --> 00:16:06,500
 And you would come now and give us understanding,

425
00:16:06,500 --> 00:16:08,120
 open our ears,

426
00:16:08,120 --> 00:16:11,200
 allow us to hear what you have to say to us this morning.

427
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:14,580
 In Jesus' name, amen.

428
00:16:14,580 --> 00:16:18,000
 The picture Zachariah has given

429
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:23,000
 is this picture of these trees and these lampstands.

430
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:25,540
 And there's this oil that's flowing through it.

431
00:16:25,540 --> 00:16:27,780
 The lampstands really don't have a purpose

432
00:16:27,780 --> 00:16:29,380
 if the oil isn't flowing through it.

433
00:16:29,380 --> 00:16:32,100
 So the oil is flowing through it from the trees,

434
00:16:32,100 --> 00:16:34,400
 one on the left and one on the right.

435
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:39,400
 This is God's response to 20 years

436
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:42,860
 of no one working on the thing that he called them to do.

437
00:16:42,860 --> 00:16:45,420
 He gives them a picture of trees and lampstands.

438
00:16:47,920 --> 00:16:51,460
 God sees that for 20 years they've struggled so much,

439
00:16:51,460 --> 00:16:53,620
 they've quit, they just let it go.

440
00:16:53,620 --> 00:16:58,180
 And his response is trees and lampstand and oil.

441
00:16:58,180 --> 00:17:04,960
 He understood that they felt like they had no way to finish

442
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:06,880
 what he had commissioned them into.

443
00:17:06,880 --> 00:17:11,260
 He understood that they had obstacles,

444
00:17:11,260 --> 00:17:14,420
 they had run out of strength, out of ability.

445
00:17:14,420 --> 00:17:15,860
 And God's response is this,

446
00:17:15,860 --> 00:17:18,400
 that my temple will not be built by might,

447
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:20,640
 it will not be built by power,

448
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:22,860
 but it will be built by my spirit.

449
00:17:22,860 --> 00:17:27,320
 So what I wanna do today is examine these three elements

450
00:17:27,320 --> 00:17:31,060
 that God speaks on, might and power and spirit,

451
00:17:31,060 --> 00:17:32,300
 understand what they have in common,

452
00:17:32,300 --> 00:17:33,860
 what's different about them.

453
00:17:33,860 --> 00:17:37,980
 'Cause I think this can be a pretty common Christian verse

454
00:17:37,980 --> 00:17:40,700
 that we might use and hear and be inspired by,

455
00:17:40,700 --> 00:17:43,180
 but I think when we understand its context

456
00:17:43,180 --> 00:17:45,320
 and what it was meant to mean to the people then,

457
00:17:45,320 --> 00:17:47,360
 we can better understand how it's meant

458
00:17:47,360 --> 00:17:48,900
 to speak to us today.

459
00:17:48,900 --> 00:17:54,660
 The first word is bechola.

460
00:17:54,660 --> 00:17:59,360
 This is the Hebrew word that speaks of strength.

461
00:17:59,360 --> 00:18:04,140
 It speaks of power, but it speaks of the individual power,

462
00:18:04,140 --> 00:18:07,620
 the individual strength, the individual abilities

463
00:18:07,620 --> 00:18:10,960
 and competencies and skills that one might have.

464
00:18:10,960 --> 00:18:14,220
 It's the quality of being able to perform,

465
00:18:14,220 --> 00:18:17,100
 especially a quality that permits your achieving

466
00:18:17,100 --> 00:18:17,940
 or accomplishing.

467
00:18:17,940 --> 00:18:21,220
 This is how you are able to do something.

468
00:18:21,220 --> 00:18:23,140
 So when God says not by this,

469
00:18:23,140 --> 00:18:25,840
 he's saying not by your physical ability,

470
00:18:25,840 --> 00:18:28,900
 not by how resilient you physically are

471
00:18:28,900 --> 00:18:30,900
 or how strong you are mentally,

472
00:18:30,900 --> 00:18:33,880
 not about what you can bring to the table.

473
00:18:33,880 --> 00:18:36,180
 When I read this, I hear God saying,

474
00:18:36,180 --> 00:18:40,380
 promise it's not about your gifts, as good as they are.

475
00:18:40,380 --> 00:18:42,620
 It's not about your degrees.

476
00:18:43,620 --> 00:18:47,060
 It's not by your cultural relevance,

477
00:18:47,060 --> 00:18:49,740
 which I have done 'cause I'm from America, but you know.

478
00:18:49,740 --> 00:18:54,100
 It's not by the things that you bring to the table.

479
00:18:54,100 --> 00:18:56,480
 That is not how things will get done.

480
00:18:56,480 --> 00:19:00,700
 And there's another word that shows up as well.

481
00:19:00,700 --> 00:19:01,980
 Bechayel.

482
00:19:01,980 --> 00:19:05,820
 This word speaks of wealth, of efficiency,

483
00:19:05,820 --> 00:19:07,260
 of the strength of an army.

484
00:19:07,260 --> 00:19:09,420
 So whereas the first word spoke

485
00:19:09,420 --> 00:19:11,620
 of the individual's competencies,

486
00:19:11,620 --> 00:19:14,660
 this now speaks of the general group,

487
00:19:14,660 --> 00:19:17,540
 the community's efforts, their strength,

488
00:19:17,540 --> 00:19:19,940
 what they, the sum of what all they have,

489
00:19:19,940 --> 00:19:21,660
 what they bring to the table.

490
00:19:21,660 --> 00:19:23,980
 So it's like not by your might promise,

491
00:19:23,980 --> 00:19:27,280
 also not by the vine's efforts, right?

492
00:19:27,280 --> 00:19:30,060
 The community, together we're stronger,

493
00:19:30,060 --> 00:19:32,180
 but even together we're not enough to get

494
00:19:32,180 --> 00:19:34,500
 to what God is wanting us to get to.

495
00:19:34,500 --> 00:19:40,260
 Which kind of feels discouraging, if I'm honest, right?

496
00:19:40,260 --> 00:19:43,380
 Like the collective resources, is it gonna be enough, God?

497
00:19:43,380 --> 00:19:46,100
 The strength of the nation, the strength of the community.

498
00:19:46,100 --> 00:19:48,060
 If we put all of our best foots forward,

499
00:19:48,060 --> 00:19:49,540
 we're still not enough.

500
00:19:49,540 --> 00:19:52,220
 Neither my individual strength or competencies,

501
00:19:52,220 --> 00:19:55,340
 nor our collective efforts will be enough.

502
00:19:55,340 --> 00:19:56,620
 The question that comes to mind is,

503
00:19:56,620 --> 00:19:59,340
 has God called us to things that we can't accomplish?

504
00:19:59,340 --> 00:20:03,340
 I feel like that's not really

505
00:20:03,340 --> 00:20:04,860
 a good church question, is it?

506
00:20:04,860 --> 00:20:08,180
 But I think it's one we have to wrestle with,

507
00:20:08,180 --> 00:20:10,700
 because I think there's something for us to understand

508
00:20:10,700 --> 00:20:14,380
 in this, has God led us to these visions,

509
00:20:14,380 --> 00:20:16,600
 and to these directions, and to these steps

510
00:20:16,600 --> 00:20:18,700
 that actually we can't do?

511
00:20:18,700 --> 00:20:21,320
 And if he has, why?

512
00:20:21,320 --> 00:20:23,620
 What exactly is the purpose of having a start

513
00:20:23,620 --> 00:20:24,740
 if we can't finish?

514
00:20:24,740 --> 00:20:26,040
 If we don't have the strength,

515
00:20:26,040 --> 00:20:27,300
 if we don't have the resources,

516
00:20:27,300 --> 00:20:28,520
 if we don't have the network,

517
00:20:28,520 --> 00:20:30,020
 if we don't have all the things that we need,

518
00:20:30,020 --> 00:20:33,100
 if we don't have, if by our might and by our power,

519
00:20:33,100 --> 00:20:35,880
 it's not gonna be enough to accomplish what you're doing,

520
00:20:35,880 --> 00:20:37,460
 then why?

521
00:20:38,140 --> 00:20:43,140
 Why does God start this response of his people

522
00:20:43,140 --> 00:20:46,920
 by telling them what will not work first?

523
00:20:46,920 --> 00:20:49,020
 It's rather than telling them, "Do this,"

524
00:20:49,020 --> 00:20:51,980
 he says, "Don't do this, don't do this."

525
00:20:51,980 --> 00:20:54,200
 I love the order in which he's said.

526
00:20:54,200 --> 00:20:58,880
 He starts by addressing the things

527
00:20:58,880 --> 00:21:01,120
 that we tend to put our trust in.

528
00:21:01,120 --> 00:21:02,780
 So we as human beings, naturally,

529
00:21:02,780 --> 00:21:04,540
 we're going to trust what we know works.

530
00:21:04,540 --> 00:21:07,180
 And in so many cases, having the right resources,

531
00:21:07,180 --> 00:21:10,020
 knowing the right people, having the right degrees,

532
00:21:10,020 --> 00:21:12,220
 this is how we normally get by in life, right?

533
00:21:12,220 --> 00:21:13,340
 Like, did you go to the right school?

534
00:21:13,340 --> 00:21:14,620
 Did you have the right internship?

535
00:21:14,620 --> 00:21:15,460
 Do you know the right people?

536
00:21:15,460 --> 00:21:16,740
 Did you rub shoulders with whoever?

537
00:21:16,740 --> 00:21:17,580
 Do you have enough money?

538
00:21:17,580 --> 00:21:18,620
 Do you live in this right place?

539
00:21:18,620 --> 00:21:20,500
 Then you can achieve X, Y, and Z.

540
00:21:20,500 --> 00:21:22,820
 That's the metric that we normally live in.

541
00:21:22,820 --> 00:21:25,160
 And God's like, "Actually, that's irrelevant.

542
00:21:25,160 --> 00:21:27,660
 "It doesn't matter."

543
00:21:27,660 --> 00:21:31,060
 He starts by telling us that we don't need

544
00:21:31,060 --> 00:21:33,460
 to trust those things.

545
00:21:33,460 --> 00:21:36,180
 We don't need to rely on those things.

546
00:21:36,180 --> 00:21:37,620
 Let's understand this.

547
00:21:37,620 --> 00:21:40,900
 God is saying they're irrelevant in accomplishing

548
00:21:40,900 --> 00:21:42,460
 his goals if we depend on them.

549
00:21:42,460 --> 00:21:44,060
 He's not saying that we can't have them.

550
00:21:44,060 --> 00:21:46,100
 So God's not saying, "Give up all your resources.

551
00:21:46,100 --> 00:21:47,060
 "Give up all your strength.

552
00:21:47,060 --> 00:21:48,280
 "Just completely be limp."

553
00:21:48,280 --> 00:21:50,460
 That's not the Bible.

554
00:21:50,460 --> 00:21:53,180
 However, what we rely on versus what we have

555
00:21:53,180 --> 00:21:54,420
 are two different things.

556
00:21:54,420 --> 00:21:59,720
 We as people, the temptation is to put our trust

557
00:21:59,720 --> 00:22:01,100
 in these things.

558
00:22:01,100 --> 00:22:03,140
 And God is saying this, that all those things,

559
00:22:03,140 --> 00:22:04,860
 might, and power, and strength,

560
00:22:04,860 --> 00:22:06,820
 and things you can accumulate,

561
00:22:06,820 --> 00:22:09,420
 and all the things that you have,

562
00:22:09,420 --> 00:22:11,560
 they make pretty crummy gods.

563
00:22:11,560 --> 00:22:17,200
 They aren't meant to be depended on.

564
00:22:17,200 --> 00:22:21,280
 They're not meant to be relied on.

565
00:22:21,280 --> 00:22:28,020
 It's not by them that you accomplish the things of God.

566
00:22:28,020 --> 00:22:32,500
 So you use your resources, use your strength,

567
00:22:32,500 --> 00:22:37,500
 use your wealth, but rely on, depend on, and trust in God.

568
00:22:37,500 --> 00:22:43,580
 This is the course correction he's making.

569
00:22:43,580 --> 00:22:44,860
 He's not saying one is bad, one is good.

570
00:22:44,860 --> 00:22:48,500
 He's saying only one of these can be relied on.

571
00:22:48,500 --> 00:22:52,020
 Only one of these is big enough for you to depend on,

572
00:22:52,020 --> 00:22:55,080
 for you to put your faith and your trust in.

573
00:22:55,080 --> 00:22:59,540
 When we start to trust and depend on our resources,

574
00:22:59,540 --> 00:23:00,700
 what ends up happening?

575
00:23:01,260 --> 00:23:04,700
 I found this very profound for me.

576
00:23:04,700 --> 00:23:05,620
 It may not be profound for you,

577
00:23:05,620 --> 00:23:08,600
 but as I was studying this, it really wrestled with my head.

578
00:23:08,600 --> 00:23:11,200
 When we start to depend on our resources,

579
00:23:11,200 --> 00:23:13,120
 and the things that we have, by nature,

580
00:23:13,120 --> 00:23:16,140
 we then start to determine what is possible

581
00:23:16,140 --> 00:23:17,460
 based off of what we have.

582
00:23:17,460 --> 00:23:21,500
 If I have enough of this, I can go this far.

583
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:24,000
 If I've accumulated this, I can now do this.

584
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:26,980
 It doesn't work for God.

585
00:23:26,980 --> 00:23:30,540
 You can't use your resources, and your might,

586
00:23:30,540 --> 00:23:32,820
 and your strength to determine

587
00:23:32,820 --> 00:23:34,220
 if God wants you to go somewhere.

588
00:23:34,220 --> 00:23:35,900
 What happens when God calls you to go somewhere

589
00:23:35,900 --> 00:23:37,380
 and you don't have the resources?

590
00:23:37,380 --> 00:23:38,860
 Must not be God?

591
00:23:38,860 --> 00:23:41,900
 Ooh, but we have so many stories of God just saying,

592
00:23:41,900 --> 00:23:43,780
 "Get up, Abraham, and go."

593
00:23:43,780 --> 00:23:46,460
 Where's he going?

594
00:23:46,460 --> 00:23:47,280
 I don't know.

595
00:23:47,280 --> 00:23:49,380
 Leave everything behind.

596
00:23:49,380 --> 00:23:51,660
 To disciples, just forget about mother and father,

597
00:23:51,660 --> 00:23:53,980
 forget about bearing a dead, forget about fixing your cattle,

598
00:23:53,980 --> 00:23:56,400
 forget about your farm, come and follow me.

599
00:23:56,400 --> 00:24:00,260
 He says, "Forget about the stuff."

600
00:24:00,260 --> 00:24:03,140
 So we don't determine if God has called us into a season.

601
00:24:03,140 --> 00:24:05,900
 We don't determine if we should stay and fight

602
00:24:05,900 --> 00:24:07,500
 based off of what we have.

603
00:24:07,500 --> 00:24:09,660
 We determine if we should stay in it

604
00:24:09,660 --> 00:24:12,100
 based off of who we have.

605
00:24:12,100 --> 00:24:14,800
 And who do we have?

606
00:24:14,800 --> 00:24:18,460
 Who has been given to us?

607
00:24:18,460 --> 00:24:21,460
 It's not by might, it's not by power,

608
00:24:21,460 --> 00:24:26,460
 but it's by the Spirit, by my Spirit.

609
00:24:29,220 --> 00:24:32,580
 I was, I don't know why I keep sharing this detail.

610
00:24:32,580 --> 00:24:37,580
 So when I connect with God and I hear him speak,

611
00:24:37,580 --> 00:24:40,240
 there's a place in my house that it happens at most.

612
00:24:40,240 --> 00:24:42,280
 That place happens to be in the shower.

613
00:24:42,280 --> 00:24:44,960
 I don't know why, but God just likes to talk a lot

614
00:24:44,960 --> 00:24:47,100
 when I have really hot water running on my body.

615
00:24:47,100 --> 00:24:50,140
 So last night, I'm getting ready, I'm praying,

616
00:24:50,140 --> 00:24:52,860
 and I'm taking a shower, and God starts like,

617
00:24:52,860 --> 00:24:54,700
 I don't know, it's kind of like downloading some things

618
00:24:54,700 --> 00:24:55,980
 that I didn't write into my sermon.

619
00:24:55,980 --> 00:24:57,620
 So this is off-script production.

620
00:24:58,460 --> 00:25:01,780
 But he was giving me this clear picture

621
00:25:01,780 --> 00:25:06,780
 of the difference that separates might, power,

622
00:25:06,780 --> 00:25:09,740
 and Spirit of God.

623
00:25:09,740 --> 00:25:11,940
 So when it comes to might and power,

624
00:25:11,940 --> 00:25:15,420
 those things naturally put you in a posture of taking.

625
00:25:15,420 --> 00:25:17,180
 With your might, you can achieve these things.

626
00:25:17,180 --> 00:25:18,340
 You can reach these things.

627
00:25:18,340 --> 00:25:20,940
 With your power, you can get this, you can grab this,

628
00:25:20,940 --> 00:25:23,580
 you can achieve, you can take for yourself.

629
00:25:23,580 --> 00:25:26,940
 The Spirit of God cannot be taken.

630
00:25:27,940 --> 00:25:31,700
 It's a small detail, but the Spirit of God cannot,

631
00:25:31,700 --> 00:25:35,100
 you can't might enough to get the Spirit of God.

632
00:25:35,100 --> 00:25:37,680
 Or the gifts of God, they are received,

633
00:25:37,680 --> 00:25:40,220
 they are bestowed upon us.

634
00:25:40,220 --> 00:25:43,500
 And the posture that we carry will determine

635
00:25:43,500 --> 00:25:45,540
 which of those things that we're doing.

636
00:25:45,540 --> 00:25:47,940
 Are we trying to get to the things of God

637
00:25:47,940 --> 00:25:50,780
 by taking and reaching and aiming and striving,

638
00:25:50,780 --> 00:25:53,300
 or have we postured ourselves enough

639
00:25:53,300 --> 00:25:56,500
 to receive strength from him?

640
00:25:56,500 --> 00:25:59,060
 To receive the gifts that he gives

641
00:25:59,060 --> 00:26:01,900
 that helps us to accomplish the things that he wants?

642
00:26:01,900 --> 00:26:06,220
 Even the endurance to withstand years upon years

643
00:26:06,220 --> 00:26:07,460
 of having to wait.

644
00:26:07,460 --> 00:26:15,220
 Is our posture receiving, or is our posture taking?

645
00:26:15,220 --> 00:26:17,620
 Is our posture by might and power and strength,

646
00:26:17,620 --> 00:26:21,260
 or is it by receiving what the Spirit has for us?

647
00:26:21,260 --> 00:26:24,100
 He says, "But by my Spirit."

648
00:26:24,100 --> 00:26:27,140
 It's one of the things that I love that God doesn't do here.

649
00:26:27,140 --> 00:26:28,580
 I love it, but I hate it at the same time,

650
00:26:28,580 --> 00:26:29,740
 so I'm kind of torn about it.

651
00:26:29,740 --> 00:26:32,860
 He doesn't promise that the obstacles are gonna go away.

652
00:26:32,860 --> 00:26:35,940
 Like I would really love if this verse was like,

653
00:26:35,940 --> 00:26:38,060
 "Not by power, not by might,

654
00:26:38,060 --> 00:26:40,580
 "all the problems are gonna go away because of my Spirit."

655
00:26:40,580 --> 00:26:42,420
 Like I don't have tattoos, but that would be one

656
00:26:42,420 --> 00:26:44,380
 that I would put on my body immediately.

657
00:26:44,380 --> 00:26:45,860
 Right, like if he just promised

658
00:26:45,860 --> 00:26:48,460
 that all the problems are gonna go away, he does it.

659
00:26:50,100 --> 00:26:54,540
 By my Spirit, but the obstacles are still gonna come.

660
00:26:54,540 --> 00:26:57,260
 I think it's a bit of a reality check for us sometimes,

661
00:26:57,260 --> 00:26:58,620
 that even with the Spirit of God,

662
00:26:58,620 --> 00:27:02,100
 you will still face tribulations.

663
00:27:02,100 --> 00:27:04,100
 You will still face obstacles.

664
00:27:04,100 --> 00:27:08,460
 You will still face resistance in the very thing

665
00:27:08,460 --> 00:27:10,640
 that God has called you into.

666
00:27:10,640 --> 00:27:13,060
 And how do we make it through that?

667
00:27:13,060 --> 00:27:16,000
 And it won't be by our might.

668
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:18,100
 It won't be by what we have.

669
00:27:18,100 --> 00:27:21,340
 It won't be by our collective strength.

670
00:27:21,340 --> 00:27:25,300
 It will be by his power, by his Spirit.

671
00:27:25,300 --> 00:27:28,980
 To an extent, he says might and power are irrelevant

672
00:27:28,980 --> 00:27:31,940
 when compared to the Spirit of God,

673
00:27:31,940 --> 00:27:33,500
 which might sound kind of crazy to say,

674
00:27:33,500 --> 00:27:37,220
 but there's exponentially greater value

675
00:27:37,220 --> 00:27:40,400
 in the confidence of the Spirit with us

676
00:27:40,400 --> 00:27:43,120
 than having all the resources we think we need.

677
00:27:43,120 --> 00:27:47,020
 If you know the Spirit,

678
00:27:47,020 --> 00:27:48,780
 you know this statement to be true.

679
00:27:48,780 --> 00:27:53,580
 During the 9/15, end of 9/15,

680
00:27:53,580 --> 00:27:55,460
 I was talking with somebody and he hit me again.

681
00:27:55,460 --> 00:27:57,420
 I'm like, I kind of wish God would tell me

682
00:27:57,420 --> 00:27:59,260
 all these things beforehand so I could write them all

683
00:27:59,260 --> 00:28:00,940
 into the sermon and it could flow pretty,

684
00:28:00,940 --> 00:28:02,940
 but he doesn't, he just kind of tells me randomly.

685
00:28:02,940 --> 00:28:03,940
 So another thought came to mind,

686
00:28:03,940 --> 00:28:05,460
 so I thought I'd share it with you guys as well.

687
00:28:05,460 --> 00:28:07,700
 Might and power and strength,

688
00:28:07,700 --> 00:28:11,860
 all of those are finite resources.

689
00:28:11,860 --> 00:28:15,620
 Resources end.

690
00:28:15,620 --> 00:28:16,820
 They don't go on forever.

691
00:28:16,820 --> 00:28:19,240
 Like half of our world is in so much chaos

692
00:28:19,240 --> 00:28:21,020
 because we're fighting for resources.

693
00:28:21,020 --> 00:28:23,540
 We're using our might and our power to hoard these things.

694
00:28:23,540 --> 00:28:26,860
 The Spirit of God, that picture of the olive tree

695
00:28:26,860 --> 00:28:29,480
 and the olive oil just overflowing,

696
00:28:29,480 --> 00:28:32,240
 there is no end to him.

697
00:28:32,240 --> 00:28:36,500
 He's the beginning and he's the end.

698
00:28:36,500 --> 00:28:41,020
 What he can do with or without our resources

699
00:28:41,020 --> 00:28:42,920
 is abundantly bigger than anything

700
00:28:42,920 --> 00:28:45,620
 that we could accommodate for ourselves.

701
00:28:45,620 --> 00:28:47,180
 I'm saying all this just to say,

702
00:28:47,180 --> 00:28:51,700
 don't count God out because you don't have

703
00:28:51,700 --> 00:28:54,660
 the stuff you need to keep following him.

704
00:28:54,660 --> 00:28:59,100
 Don't count him out because your job doesn't pay well enough

705
00:28:59,100 --> 00:29:01,580
 or you don't know the language of the city

706
00:29:01,580 --> 00:29:02,420
 that you're moving to.

707
00:29:02,420 --> 00:29:03,980
 That sounds crazy.

708
00:29:03,980 --> 00:29:05,700
 Like I moved to Hong Kong, I've shared it too many times,

709
00:29:05,700 --> 00:29:06,540
 so I won't go into details,

710
00:29:06,540 --> 00:29:08,280
 but I came here only knowing about rush hour.

711
00:29:08,280 --> 00:29:09,580
 I knew nothing about this city

712
00:29:09,580 --> 00:29:11,580
 and I've been here for 12 years now.

713
00:29:11,580 --> 00:29:12,980
 Like don't count God out

714
00:29:12,980 --> 00:29:15,380
 because you don't have the resources.

715
00:29:15,380 --> 00:29:17,140
 Don't count God out because you don't have

716
00:29:17,140 --> 00:29:20,160
 the physical strength or the ability or the skill set

717
00:29:20,160 --> 00:29:22,960
 or the networking or the you name the thing.

718
00:29:22,960 --> 00:29:29,300
 No, we don't determine his calling

719
00:29:29,300 --> 00:29:33,460
 and his desire for us to endure based off of what we have,

720
00:29:33,460 --> 00:29:36,020
 but it's by his spirit.

721
00:29:36,020 --> 00:29:39,120
 That's the key to this whole thing.

722
00:29:39,120 --> 00:29:42,500
 You think about how Jesus would call his disciples,

723
00:29:42,500 --> 00:29:45,820
 follow me, gave them nothing, just said follow me.

724
00:29:45,820 --> 00:29:47,120
 Think about if you've been here at the Vine

725
00:29:47,120 --> 00:29:49,660
 for the past year, the one word that has been

726
00:29:49,660 --> 00:29:52,500
 in like every sermon series is uncharted, right?

727
00:29:52,500 --> 00:29:54,700
 This uncharted territories, uncharted waters,

728
00:29:54,700 --> 00:29:55,940
 uncharted everything.

729
00:29:55,940 --> 00:29:57,940
 This idea that God is calling us into a space

730
00:29:57,940 --> 00:29:59,980
 that we do not know as a community,

731
00:29:59,980 --> 00:30:02,300
 a space where our maps and our navigational tools

732
00:30:02,300 --> 00:30:04,380
 aren't gonna be able to help us,

733
00:30:04,380 --> 00:30:08,060
 where our resources aren't gonna be able to be relied upon,

734
00:30:08,060 --> 00:30:09,680
 where we're not gonna have a strategy

735
00:30:09,680 --> 00:30:11,760
 that we can fall back on.

736
00:30:12,600 --> 00:30:16,960
 But instead we're gonna have to trust in him,

737
00:30:16,960 --> 00:30:19,440
 which is a terrifying yet liberating thing.

738
00:30:19,440 --> 00:30:21,680
 So let me reframe the slightly controversial question

739
00:30:21,680 --> 00:30:23,160
 I asked earlier and put it this way.

740
00:30:23,160 --> 00:30:26,120
 Has God called us into things bigger

741
00:30:26,120 --> 00:30:28,500
 than we ourselves could accomplish?

742
00:30:28,500 --> 00:30:30,480
 See, it's a little bit different

743
00:30:30,480 --> 00:30:32,520
 when you look at it that way.

744
00:30:32,520 --> 00:30:35,280
 It's more about what he wants to do

745
00:30:35,280 --> 00:30:37,800
 and less about how able we are,

746
00:30:37,800 --> 00:30:40,800
 which is the predominant posture we should carry

747
00:30:40,800 --> 00:30:43,060
 into this new year.

748
00:30:43,060 --> 00:30:44,840
 If God is calling you to endure a thing,

749
00:30:44,840 --> 00:30:49,180
 if he's calling you to stay in a moment, to continue,

750
00:30:49,180 --> 00:30:53,200
 it's less about your ability and so much more

751
00:30:53,200 --> 00:30:56,020
 about what he is able to do.

752
00:30:56,020 --> 00:31:04,980
 I'm gonna skip ahead production.

753
00:31:04,980 --> 00:31:09,800
 I read this and I think, take the pressure off.

754
00:31:10,800 --> 00:31:13,860
 It's up to God to accomplish what's gonna happen.

755
00:31:13,860 --> 00:31:16,380
 You can breathe.

756
00:31:16,380 --> 00:31:19,600
 I mean, I know it's hard, but we can breathe.

757
00:31:19,600 --> 00:31:20,720
 It's not up to us.

758
00:31:20,720 --> 00:31:24,640
 We were never strong enough to begin with, you know?

759
00:31:24,640 --> 00:31:26,560
 We've always, always needed him.

760
00:31:26,560 --> 00:31:32,960
 So allow that breath to give you strength again.

761
00:31:32,960 --> 00:31:34,300
 God's got it.

762
00:31:34,300 --> 00:31:36,120
 I think this is why Paul can say things like

763
00:31:36,120 --> 00:31:39,740
 in 2 Corinthians that God's strength is made perfect

764
00:31:39,740 --> 00:31:40,600
 in our weakness.

765
00:31:40,600 --> 00:31:42,880
 Now, it doesn't matter how strong I am,

766
00:31:42,880 --> 00:31:46,840
 but I boast in my weakness because I know who is strong

767
00:31:46,840 --> 00:31:48,160
 and I know who is with me.

768
00:31:48,160 --> 00:31:49,800
 So if I don't have the ability,

769
00:31:49,800 --> 00:31:52,920
 but the God of the universe now resides his presence,

770
00:31:52,920 --> 00:31:56,060
 his temple, his dwelling place is inside of me,

771
00:31:56,060 --> 00:31:59,560
 then technically I can do all things through Christ

772
00:31:59,560 --> 00:32:02,260
 who strengthens me, amen?

773
00:32:02,260 --> 00:32:04,560
 Because of he who is in us.

774
00:32:04,560 --> 00:32:06,320
 Greater, so many scriptures come to mind,

775
00:32:06,320 --> 00:32:08,720
 but greater is he who is in us

776
00:32:08,720 --> 00:32:10,780
 than he who is in the obstacle that's coming.

777
00:32:10,780 --> 00:32:12,720
 Greater is he who is in us

778
00:32:12,720 --> 00:32:15,200
 than he who is in the waiting for years upon years.

779
00:32:15,200 --> 00:32:18,560
 Greater is he who is within us

780
00:32:18,560 --> 00:32:20,040
 than he who is within the world.

781
00:32:20,040 --> 00:32:23,920
 Guys, we've got something great inside of us.

782
00:32:23,920 --> 00:32:25,860
 The Holy Spirit.

783
00:32:25,860 --> 00:32:28,140
 I just wish, like I can't fully comprehend it,

784
00:32:28,140 --> 00:32:30,360
 but I wish we could all comprehend it more,

785
00:32:30,360 --> 00:32:34,040
 that the God of the universe, his spirit, his essence,

786
00:32:34,040 --> 00:32:37,120
